  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Amongst the challenges of text production is finding the lexical items appropriate for the expression of the intended meaning.",
    "These lexical items may well be known to the speaker, but recalling (retrieving) them may be difficult.",
    "Then there is the issue of using conventional constructions for the given lexical item, as well as natural collocations (that is, conventional co-occurrences of words).",
    "The last point is particularly tricky for non-native writers, even advanced ones, but, as it turns out, also for native writers when faced with a specific text genre such as academic English (Hyland and Shaw, 2016, Frankenberg-Garcia, 2018).",
    "Until a few decades ago, spelling may have been a problem, but spellcheckers built into text editors and word processors had gradually and largely taken over the task."
  ],
